HEADWORD: Sectator
<hw>Sec*ta"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>sectari</ets>, v. intens. fr. <ets>sequi</ets> to follow. See
<er>Sue</er> to follow.]</ety> <def>A follower; a disciple; an adherent
to a sect.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir W.
Raleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

